By Adepote Arowojobe Ikorodu – An Ikorodu Chief Magistrates’ Court on Wednesday granted a N100, 000 bail each to two men who allegedly stole packets of chewing gum, sweet and  rubber band  valued at N2, 200. The defendants, Ifeoluwa Olatunji (20) and Shefiu Oluwatobi (18) were
granted bail by the Magistrate, Mrs A. R. Onilogbo after their
arraignment by the Police for allegedly breaking into a shop and
stealing the items. The defendants, whose addresses were not known, are facing three-count charge bordering on felony, burglary and stealing. The Prosecutor, ASP Gbemileke Agoi, had told the court that the
accused burgled the store belonging to one Mamuda Abubakar at Ota-Ona in
Ikorodu. Agoi said that the defendants stole one packet of sweet valued at N1,
000, one packet of chewing gum valued at N1, 000 and one packet of
rubber band valued N200. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the offences
contravened Sections 411, 309(2) and 287 of the Criminal Law of Lagos
State, 2015. The defendants, however, pleaded not guilty to the charges. The Magistrate, Mrs A. R. Onilogbo, granted the defendants N100, 000 bail each with two responsible sureties in like sum. The case was adjourned until May 16, for mention.